               <head>Maslak al-muttaqiyyin</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_15657-item1" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008124217">
                     <author>Allāh Yār Khan Bukhārīالله يار خان بخارى</author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Maslak al-muttaqīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">مسلك المتقين</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A lengthy didactic poem on aspects of theology and law by Ṣūfī Allāhyār (or Ilāhyār) Khan Bukhārī (fl. 1050/1640).</p>
                        <p>Contents: introduction, on Islamic doctrine, and four books concerning purification, ritual prayer, zakāt and fasting according to Ḥanafī fiqh.</p>
                        <p>Book 1 was completed in 1111/1699, Book 2 the following year.</p>
                        <p>Colophon, f. 396v. Copied at the Ādīnah (Friday) Madrasa at Faizabad, in Badakhshan, Afghanistan, by Ḥabīb Allāh ibn Mullā ‘Āshūr Muḥammad. Completed at breakfast time on Friday 19 Safar<corr>Ṣafar</corr>1284/22 June 1867.</p>
                        <p>Other contents: front endpaper and f. 1r, owners’ scribbles; 1r, ownership inscription dated 1339/1920-21; 396v, note of a payment and a bayt of verse.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="" xml:lang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
